    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Symphytum officinale are sprains, which are relieved by its anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties, as well as bruises and wounds, which are accelerated in healing due to its mucilaginous and soothing effects. It is also effective in treating inflammation, arthritis, and tendinitis, as the plant contains allantoin, a compound that promotes cell regeneration and collagen synthesis. Additionally, it is used to treat gout, bursitis, and rheumatism, as its anti-inflammatory and pain-relieving properties help reduce swelling and alleviate joint pain. Furthermore, Symphytum officinale has been found to be beneficial in treating muscle spasms, wound healing, muscle pain, and cuts, due to its ability to reduce inflammation and promote tissue repair. Its anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties also make it effective in treating burns and skin irritation, such as eczema, by reducing redness and promoting wound healing.",
