    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Symphytum officinale are its anti-inflammatory activity, which is attributed to the presence of saponins that inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory cytokines and enzymes. Additionally, the plant exhibits analgesic properties due to the action of volatile oils, such as borneol and bornyl acetate, which have been shown to have a direct effect on the nervous system to reduce pain perception. The antioxidant properties of Symphytum officinale are largely attributed to flavonoids, which scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. Furthermore, the plant's antimicrobial properties are attributed to the presence of sesquiterpenes and phenolic acids, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of a wide range of microorganisms. The plant's ability to promote wound healing is also attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, which stimulate collagen synthesis and tissue repair, respectively.",
