    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Symphytum officinale improperly include experience nausea and nauseate due to its emetic properties which can cause vomiting when taken in high doses. Abdominal pain is also a potential side effect as the plant contains saponins and other compounds that can irritate the digestive tract. Allergic reactions such as hives, itching, and difficulty breathing can occur in individuals who are sensitive to the plant's allergenic compounds. Furthermore, diarrhea is a possible side effect due to the plant's ability to increase gut motility and stimulate bowel movements. The improper use of Symphytum officinale can lead to these side effects because it is often used in herbal preparations without adequate quality control and standardized dosing."
